burnout III - no other buffs in all instances.<br>
<br>
killing sun revenants in scarlet.<br>
<br>
epic with no armor and no ds got its ass handed to it.<br>
epic with phantom plate and no ds lasted noticably longer than the first, but still lost.<br>
epic with no armor and ds won comfortably.<br>
epic with armor and ds beat the snot out of the npc (67% health left)<br>
<br>
I hand my pet 4 pieces of armor at a time, he seems to wear all of it.  I hand him 2 sor's and he will equip them both, so logic would dictate he will equip all pieces if handed more than one at a time.  You can also give your pet an elemental defender, and he will equip it.  Keep in mind you have to give him weapons first, if you want him to put it in the back slot, otherwise it will be equipped as a shield.<br>
<br>
An item of note - with the SoL graphics turned on, the pet attack animation is with the left hand, meaning you will only see the pet attack graphics if the pet makes the dual wield roll.  Earth is the only exception.<br>
<br>
Pets do wear armor if you give it to them, and it does make some difference...particularly if soloing.<br>
